dor Found</span><hr size=1> Now to find Arantir Karondor. I honestly have no idea what Verant was thinking when they did this part of the quest. There are zero clues as to who or where this person is and honestly, it's sort of disturbing to me that every other class' quest is straightforward, but still has a very good degree of difficulty. None the less, there is a female NPC vendor in Halas named 'Dargon' that sells a potion called Ro's Breath (8 Charges of Shield of Lava, MAGIC, LORE, NO DROP). She is located in front of the Shaman guild. Purchase this potion from Dargon (evil races be warned - you ARE KOS!) for the sum of about 900pp depending on your faction and charisma (bring 1000pp to be sure).<br>
<br>
Now take this potion back to Camin in Erudin and hand it to him. He will reply with some info (looking for someone to submit their eqlog.txt for this), give you the potion back, and tell you to give the potion back to Dargon in Halas.<br>
Note: you cannot skip the previous trip to Camin. You absolutely, must hand the potion to Camin. If you do not and try to skip the trip to Erudin, you will get the following message from Dargon: "I didnt request this item, but thank you very much".<br>
<br>
Back in Halas, hand the Ro's Breath' potion back to Dargon. She will turn into blue robe adorned, Arantir Karondor and reply with some information (looking for someone to submit their eqlog.txt for this) telling you to find a woman named Challice and give her a ring that Arantir hands you.<br>
<br>
Challice is found in the basement of the Felwithe paladin guild. Hand Challice the ring and she will hand it back to you, telling you to take the ring back to Arantir Karondor in Halas (looking for someone to submit their eqlog.txt for this).<br>
<br>
Take the ring back to Arantir and hand it over (pray that Arantir is there and not Dargon or you will have to wait for another wizard to do the first part or hand Dargon the Ro's Breath again). Then you must hail him to get his attention and go through the following dialogue:<br>
<br>
you say, 'I want to hear your story.'<br>
Arantir Karondor says 'I once was one of four true followers of Solusek Ro. So great were the four of us that Solusek Ro himself made us each a special item. We did not know what the others' items were, but we realized that was for our own safety. Each one of us, after receiving the item, began to plot against Solusek Ro. Each of us believed we had enough power to dominate Norrath. Solusek Ro saw this and at the time we needed our powers most, he stripped us of them. Now I know two of the other wizards by name. One was called Sylen Tyrn, the other's name was Demunir Scry. The last wizard was a gnome, but I can't think of his name.<br>
<br>
you say, 'What about Sylen Tyrn?'<br>
Arantir Karondor says 'Sylen was a high elf wizard, and like many high elves, he believed himself to be better than others. Because of his birth, he thought he was more noble and more intelligent than anyone else. I heard how met his demise - while flying over a vast area of water, his powers were stripped from him in midflight. He fell and was captured by a rival wizard who specialized in magics of the water. Search for that wizard and you could find a trace of Sylen.<br>
<br>
More than likely, the 'trace' of Sylen Tyrn is found off of Phiningel Autropos deep in Kedge Keep - the Blue Crystal Staff. When this item is identified, the power of Solusek Ro radiates from within.<br>
<br>
you say, 'What about Demunir Scry?'<br>
Arantir Karondor says 'Demunir was a human in a rush for power. He was extremely intelligent and resourceful but, unfortunately, was more interested in destructive magic. Hearing of an ancient land, he immediately traveled to it, believing there to be powerful relics left undiscovered there. While exploring, he came upon a dwelling that housed a powerful warrior. Believing himself to be more powerful, he attempted to take this dwelling for himself. While in battle with this warrior, Solusek Ro stole his powers and left him helpless. It is said that Demunir's item is the warrior's most prized trophy.<br>
<br>
The Demunir item is thought to either be the Gnarled Staff off of Venril Sathir from within Karnor's Castle or a warrior item found from deep within The Hole.<br>
<br>
you say, 'What about gnome?'<br>
Arantir Karondor says 'Ah, the gnome I know very little about. I know he was small and crafty, and that he had a brother. His brother's craft was that of making fireworks, and he was the unfortunate victim of one of his own experiments. His firework exploded, leaving his mind diminished in capacity, even for a gnome. I remember others calling him 'Old Stewpot' in jest. I do not know if this is his birth name, but it may help you to locate him. I hear he also stays close to water because of the explosion. You never know when another gnomish invention will go awry. Give him this letter to help motivate him to remember. <br>
<br>
